<item>
            <title>[OAK-10259] oak-core tests running out of memory</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OAK-10259</link>
                <project id="12313221" key="OAK">Jackrabbit Oak</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Recently tests for oak-core were running out of memory on Jenkins. Analyzing a heap dump showed majority of heap (300 MB) retained by Mockito. It looks like this is related to &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/mockito/mockito/pull/1619&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/mockito/mockito/pull/1619&lt;/a&gt; and with &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OAK-10173&quot; title=&quot;Allow configured principals to impersonate any user&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;OAK-10173&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;OAK-10173&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; we enabled mock-maker-inline.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="13537433">OAK-10259</key>
            <summary>oak-core tests running out of memory</summary>
